Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of Twitter data to infer demographic and political attributes of users. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of data mining techniques to extract information from Twitter data. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of social media data to infer social and political attributes of users. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze Twitter data. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implications of inferring demographic and political attributes from social media data for businesses and legal investigations.
